The need for speed The Run fights across America.
Revision
Originally a problem-free race is transformed by a set of stupid mistakes of people who have nothing to do with it into a routine morning shift to work.
It fulfils everyone's ambition to some extent, but it is useless if no one wants to do something more.
The new subtitled part The Run produced great expectations before its release.
He promised to take a new direction with the already old Need for Speed race series and to release a kind of game from playable games that would not only count with points.
So we were curious how the added passages will be in which the main hero comes out of his car and does what he wants.
As is already done in the NFS series, the result is completely different from what we were looking for.
These are potentially arcade racing games but the whole pulls down because of some unnecessary mistakes that have already existed for several years.
These are not really mistakes but rather the expression of an incomprehensible lazyness on the part of the developers.
The adventure starts very well.
You are caught in the adventure whose main hero Jack has character problems and to solve them begins to participate in illegal races across America.
You sit behind the wheel on the west coast in San Francisco and your mission is to arrive first in New York.
The idea has interesting elements.
The route is divided into ten stages and then into more than 50 races.
The result is that each race takes place on another route and the stages planned in different environments that are quite distinct from each other and interesting.
The player does not feel for a single moment that the game offers him something identical.
Some environments are pretty superish even though the graphic technical level is of the same type as the previous series.
Well, that's not the end of the world.
But driving through the desert, in autumn landscapes or in highly snowy mountains is very pleasant visually.
The tests are in addition from time to time accompanied by an atypical element.
For example, in the desert you find yourself in a sandstorm that significantly reduces your visibility.
Then in the mountains you have to be careful that an avalanche doesn't fall on you.
Next to this, the different races are well organized behind each other.
There are only a few, but that is enough.
There are moments when you try to surpass the requested number of opponents (as in a classic race) and then you run against the clock (classical duel with the stopwatch) and then you wait for another duel with an opponent.
From time to time you also have the police entering the game and trying to make you dificient.
The novelty is the off-vehicle passages.
It's more like an interactive animation when most of the time Jack runs away in front of someone and you have to help him by typing the right button at the right time.
Nothing complicated.
What is surprising is that there are fewer times of this type than you expect (to be concrete there are only three).
The result is that this element is not likely to interfere and is placed, in the context described above, in the elements that enhance the game.
The driving pattern is in the tradition of previous games.
This means that at present there is nothing extraordinary but it cannot be said to be negative.
As far as realistic simulation is concerned, you will have to go elsewhere.
But although one can find better in the competition the driving model goes very well with the type of design of the races.
So everything's okay.
Problems begin to appear after a while.
At the diffference of the driving model, that of collisions is not yet perfect.
We don't expect this game to cause complicated deformation and collisions, but when you don't have, during a collision with any object, the slightest idea of how your car behaves, it's not completely good.
During tight overshoots you sometimes touch each other slightly but otherwise your auto goes into crazy voltigations.
Or you'll end up in crumbs.
Thanks to the restart system this is not really a problem but it really annoys you.
The restart is done so that when you broke the figure or you came out in the set the game will take you back to the last point on the route.
But you only have 5 restarts.
When you have used the 5 restarts you have to start the game again from the beginning.
So it's more of a tool, in case something doesn't go right, than something you can really rely on.
Sometimes the restarts don't help and you have to find the solution by remembering from memory the piece of route in question.
The big thing about this game is that the same actions are found in the same places.
For example, there are certain turns that have to be made in a certain way, otherwise it does not pass.
Otherwise, you always encounter "civil" vehicles in the same configuration that you arrived first, fifth, 5 seconds ahead or one minute behind.
What makes you angry are situations when you easily see the opponent passing between two cars coming in the opposite direction and when you arrive, you have to either put yourself aside and conturn them or brake them.
It doesn't matter if you go in front of him because it's "calculated" in such a way that for the given situation it always happens very close to your nose.
Opponents have other advantages.
Throughout the game, you, you arrive in some places, again without worrying about the time, and you always have the same opponent that precedes you in the same place.
This upsets most at the end of the game when you roll on a long bridge in the opposite direction.
The opponent must at all costs pass in front of you.
When it passes in front of you it hides the view of other vehicles in the opposite direction and you collid a lot of times.
It can be understood that the goal of this game is to do something exciting and full of adrenaline, but it is clear that you get bored quickly.
And that's a shame because through a simple driving pattern the game is interesting and places with so much action that you don't have time to follow everything that's going on.
And it doesn't matter if it's because of the concept of 50 unique routes, that the order of the races is such that there is no chance of getting bored or anything else.
The original idea is the change of car during the races.
You need to pay attention to the gas pumps on the routes because you can change cars there however most of the time the one you have is enough.
The cars are divided into three categories.
Sports cars are ideal for cities, big American cars for straight motorways and super sports cars with exotic corners on very technical lines for example on yaw roads in the mountains.
And the mode of challenges, which are races in particular places you know of adventure, goes very well with the main diet of history.
You receive not only medals but also points of experience that add to your profile that is common to challenges and adventure.
When you have reached the highest driver level, different objects start unlocking:
It connects on-line with the Autolog function that inter alia compares your results with those of other players and provides you with other functions in the community.
One of the most difficult shots to understand is the situation of the last race of the adventure.
You arrive with your car in the subway tunnel (it looks like) where you drive in the darkness on the tracks (it looks like).
Your speedometer indicates you between 150 and 200 km/hour (a priori) and behind you arrive a metro train that sends you the car directly to the scrap.
In writing we had a discussion for a few days as to whether anyone really thought about creating this game or whether the authors really think we're fools.
The technical part of the game is not extra, but the visual part is generally nice and in some cases really great.
What is bothering is that in more extreme situations, imaging does not hold the level and in some cases tragically.
This applies especially to accidents with a large number of participants when a fluid imaging is no longer useful to you.
The sound part is good and the track is at choice.
In order to please as many as possible and especially the young audience, a new soundtrack was created in the "I mix everything" style, but it can be expected that no one will buy the game for music.
Impression of Need for Speed: The Run is therefore really confused.
If the game did not have these stupid mistakes we could say without fear that this is the best NFS production in recent years.
But this game gives the impression that it's not over.
The fun is really good but get ready for mistakes to hit you in the eye with the strength of an aerodrome reflector.
The Velvet Students in concert with the Charles University choirs
The Festa Academica festival offers for the third time festivities that link International Student Day with the anniversary of the Velvet Revolution with a musical part.
During the festival there are 20 choirs of higher schools and secondary classes.
The highlight of the festival is two concerts held on 17 November.
"Charles University has an important part in this festival".
"Among the choirs there is the Choir of the Faculty of Pedagogy and Humanities, in the committee of the festival seat the rector Vaclav Hampl", says the leader of the organizing team Jakub Calou.
The highlight of the festival is the concert of the Choir des lycées et classes secondaires which takes place with free admission on November 17 from 2 p.m. on the space located in front of the National Technical Library in Dejvice.
On the programme there is the composition of the well-known Czech jazzman Karel Ruzicka, Celebration Jazz mass.
In the evening the concert "Etudes de Velvet" takes place in the premises of the National House in Vinohrady during which the choirs of the higher schools and that of Charles University perform.
The aim of the Festa Academica is not only to celebrate with dignity the International Student Day and to commemorate the 22nd anniversary of the Velvet Revolution, but also to present to the public choir music of the highest level and to develop the creative cooperation of young people.
The main organiser is the Union of Czech Cheers in cooperation with Jan Kepler High School.
The entire action is led by Bohuslav Svoboda, Mayor of Prague and Vaclav Hampl, Rector of Charles University.
The festival takes place from 16 to 20 November in Prague and Pardubice.
The program also offers high-level concerts, msical meetings, student happening and other activities.
All information can be found on the festival's internet pages www.festaacademica.cz.
Vicenova, Ambassador to the European Union:
Czechs behave like negativists and Eurosceptics
"The Lisbon Treaty has radically removed the balance between the institutions"
"I didn't expect such a hard war".
"It will last 5.6 years before the situation calms down and all the players get used to their new role", this is how Milena Vicenova began her presentation at the Faculty of Law the Czech Ambassador to the European Union.
When she managed to describe the different EU bodies and their relations in such an understandable and visible way, to the point that a large number of speakers from the Faculty of Law at Charles University might envy her, she showed how seriously she takes her wordto "understandable and openly about Europe".
Vicenova paid tribute to the work of Herman Van Rompuye, the new permanent President of the European Council.
"From the beginning, the critics sounded that it is bland, that it is a round-of-leather, that it cannot fill any mission and I must say that it has cut everyone's breath because it holds its role to perfection".
"He is a man who knows how to listen to 27 member states, communicate well with them and has a clear vision of the direction to take of Europe".
She explained the new position of the High Representative for Foreign Affairs and Defence Policy as part of an answer to the question: "Who is who in the European Union?" "What phone number should I call?", so as an important step towards the uniqueness and greater readability of EU policy vis-à-vis states, as is China or India.
No one wants to ban us from syrecky (cooked cheese that smells very strong)
Vicenova has also mentioned the agenda that the European Council has lived, lives and will live in the near future.
She called the Czech Presidency two years ago a success.
The Czechs resolved the rising financial crisis, the gas crisis or organised a summit for an Eastern Partnership.
She described the fall of the gourvernement as very negative and damaged the image of the Czech Republic.
Czech representation in the EU is currently very busy.
In the words of the Ambassador, "the activity has been in full swing" not only for the Presidency but also for the financial crisis that is still being resolved.
It is also necessary to approve the Union's new septimal budget, which is becoming very complicated because of the current economic situation.
As it seems that the budget will be thin and with a view to savings, which branch will have the priority, which countries will be assisted the most, the least, everything is to be resolved in future negotiations.
Madam Ambassador recalled her slogans with which she arrived in Brussels "For an understandable Europe".
"I really don't like abbreviations, foreign words, jargons that nobody understands.
As the citizen must understand, it is true that in Brussels no one makes round or twisted pickles, bananas that are different in size or that no one has forbidden us to make syrecky."
It wants to make better use of the EU environment and see more Czechs in the European institutions.
A multi-speed Europe awaits us
According to the Ambassador the Czechs have the reputation of being Eurosceptics and people who see things only in their negative aspect more than positively.
Moreover, she is sorry to see such a small Czech representation in the European institutions.
The fault is, in her view, the result of several factors, such as the shyness of our candidates, their inability to write a letter of motivation and the weak support of the Czech side.
In addition to a successful Czech presidency, she then stressed the strength and cooperation of the Visegrad Group.
"Believe me, when the Pole, the Magyar, the Slovak come to me, this Frenchman says to me, 'Hey, what are you doing there, what is this Visegrad band doing again?' and he's not happy at all".
According to Mrs Vicenova, in the near future, the Member States are waiting for tough new rules on budgetary policy.
It is the concept of a two-speed Europe, if not a multi-speed Europe, that prevails rather than a "new European Federation".
"We have countries in the euro area and others outside the area."
"We have the Schengen area, we also have the Institute for Enhanced Cooperation".
First of all, it was said that the countries that want it and those that do not want it are cooperating with each other."
"There will be a lot of such institutes and there will be a truly two-speed Europe," says Vicenova.
From this point of view, it also appreciated the mission of the Czech Republic and Herman Van Rompuye to establish the basis for discussing all issues having an impact on the EU between all EU members and not just the same members of the Eurozone.
History of a brand:
IBM innovator begins the second century of its existence
If someone were to look for the word that expresses the IBM strategy as closely as possible, the nearest would be "the long term".
For a large audience IBM is the symbol of the technological revolution, is a firm felt to be very current and yet since its creation it has been a hundred years.
The basis for this long-term strategy was laid by the firm's first chief, visionary Thomas J. Watson Sr.
He left this slogan that many global problems can be solved if people are willing to think.
His slogan "PENSE'!" became the imprint around which the life of a giant future will develop (and also the title of the internal magazine IBM began publishing in 1935).
This was the basis of Watson's carefully developed corporate culture.
For us IBM means a long-term thought of continuous movements directed towards the future.
IBM survived a hundred years due to the fact that it always remained faithful to its core values and yet was not afraid to change all the others around it.
This has enabled us in our first century to transform technology, business and society.
We hope that in the second century we will reach even more lamented for the anniversary the current director of the firm Samuel J. Palmisano.
A well-prepared system
Watson, in the 1930s, began caring for his employees like Bata in the Czech Republic - IBM people were the only ones among the first American employees to have paid vacations, employer-paid insurance plus an elegant employee uniform and a well-developed system of rewards for inventors and commercials.
Similarly IBM has a well-developed customer relationship system.
Society was at first brilliant in discovering talents--as one of the first firms to have abolished any form of discrimination and thus could have the choice.
The current plan is completely in the spirit of the anti-discrimination strategy since it will be a woman - Virginia Rometty - who should replace Palmisano at the head of IBM.
She has been with IBM for thirty years and currently holds the position of Chief Sales, Marketing and Strategy.
IBM in recent years does what is called jamy, online brainstorming from which many future strategies and innovations come.
It is no wonder that he has a lot of ideas - in the firm there are nearly 500,000 people working.
