Casino forgives Jonás Larrazábal and he will be released
After 72 days of provisional arrest, Casino Red's legal power-holder granted pardon to the mayor's brother of Monterrey for the trial initiated against him for alleged blackmail
After 72 years of arrest, Manuel Jonás Larrazábal will be released after the founder of the Casino Red's legal power grants him forgiveness before the District's Second Criminal Court, which is following a blackmail trial against the brother of the mayor of Monterrey.
After the Royal Casino attack, Casino Red's owner, Sergio Gil García, published a series of photos and videos in which allegedly Manuel Jonás required him to pay an economic quotte for the mayor of Monterrey to allow the underground operation of the gambling house.
