The motion on the presidency of the European Commission, proposed by management, was adopted almost unanimously.
Out of 1001 delegates, only nine voted against and ten abstained.
The standing ovation of several minutes to which they were entitled, after their speeches, Angela Merkel and then, a few hours later, Wolfgang Schäuble, the very europhile finance minister, did not leave room for doubt.
